    //         title: "IRCTC norms for travel insurance norms for train passengers",
    //         content: "<p>Train journeys in India are by far the most economical option for travel. No wonder then the masses prefer this mode of transport over others. While most of us avail of an insurance during air travel, few give it a though when it comes to <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>train travel</a>. During peak and holiday seasons, most of us travel by train across the length and the breadth of the country, without giving any thought if we should buy insurance or not. Well you should be definitely thinking about train <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a> going forward as unfortunate and untimely incidents can occur anytime and anywhere. Having insurance will provide you with monetary shield in case of any untoward circumstances.</p><p>There was a time when the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> (Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation) provided all passengers with insurance at no cost, it was absolutely free. This rule has now been modified with effect from 1st September 2018. From this date onward, passengers now have the option whether to opt in for insurance or to opt out. Hence having insurance during travel is no longer mandatory. If you opt in for insurance then it does not come free anymore and the railway <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> will charge you for the same. </p><p>The good news is that you can cover each passenger for an amount of up to rupees 10 lakhs in case of any <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>train accident</a>. Robbery and other unfortunate incidents are also covered. And all this is available at a meagre cost of 68 paisa per passenger. This is as good as free. When you book a ticket with <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> either online on their website or through their mobile app you will come across the option, if you want to choose <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a> or to opt out of having <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a>. The choice is yours, but given the paltry sum of 68 paisa it is always advisable to opt in for insurance.</p><p><strong>Eligibility:</strong> </p><p><li>Only citizens of India are eligible for this <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a>. Foreigners are not included and will have to make their own separate <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a> from third party providers.</li><li>If you have children who are less than five years old, then the insurance clause does not apply to them.</li><li>The offer of 68 paisa is only available through the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> mobile app or through its website.</li><li>Third party websites that flight booking and ticketing facilities, will charge a higher premium for <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>train travel</a>. Please find out from the respective websites the cost for the same as the premiums may vary.</li></p><p><strong>Terms and Conditions:</strong></p><p><li>For a premium of 68 paisa the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a> provides the following:</li><li>On death of a passenger, the coverage is for rupees 10 lakhs</li><li>For permanent and total disability, the coverage is for rupees 10 lakhs</li><li>For partial disability, the coverage is for rupees 7.5 lakhs</li></p><p><strong>Acts and Incidents covered by the policy through the train journey:</strong></p><p><li>Robbery / looting by dacoits</li><li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Accidents</a></li><li>Violent acts and other unpleasant events</li></p><p><strong>Insurance companies tied up with <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> for the purpose of <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>travel insurance</a></strong></p> <p> <li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>ICICI Lombard General Insurance Company</a> Limited </li> <li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Shriram General Insurance</a> Company </li> <li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Royal Sundaram General Insurance</a> Co. Limited </li> </p><p><strong><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Settlement of claims</a>:</strong></p> <p><li>When you opt in for the insurance you will receive an electronic copy of the insurance document on your registered email id </li> <li>In case of any unpleasant events, you need to file a claim with the above mentioned companies as <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a> has tied up with these insurance service providers and they are the ones that are providing you with the insurance cover. You cannot file a claim directly with <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IRCTC</a>. </li> <li>When you opt in for the insurance while train ticket booking, you need to visit the website of the respective insurance provider to fill in the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>nominee</a> details. This is important, as the claim will be given to the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>nominee</a> provided you have entered his name. If you have not entered the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>nominee</a> name on the website then the claim will be provided to the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>legal heir</a>s who stake a claim. </li></p><p>Over and above the terms and conditions mentioned above, coverage up to rupees two lakhs are provided towards expenses for hospitalization and coverage up to rupees one lakh in case of transportation of the mortal remains of the passenger.</p>",
