    //         title: "Government of India Digi-Locker facility for documents",
    //         content: "<p>Everyone has documents from various government departments that are of vital importance in your life. These are documents like your passport, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>driving licence</a>, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>vehicle registration certificate</a>, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Voters identification</a> card etc. Most of us carry them around with us as they may be required to be submitted to various authorities. When you go about carrying your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>physical documents</a>, they are prone to wear and tear, or can also be misplaced or stolen. This is a huge risk not to mention the amount of trouble one will have to go through to obtain duplicates from respective authorities. </p><p>In order to do away with the need for carrying <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>physical documents</a> with us at all time, the government of India has come up with the concept of Digi-Locker which is short for <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Digital Locker</a>. This is an initiative by the government of India, for the citizens of India, who hold a valid Aadhar card to their name. The Aadhar card and the phone number that is registered with Aadhar card, has to be linked to the Digi-Locker. This is for the purpose of dual factor authentication, where you will get a One Time Password (OTP) for authenticating your access.</p><p>As the name suggests, it is an online platform for storing documents in a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>digital format</a> for individuals and organizations. Every individual gets 1 GB of storage space in the cloud, wherein you can upload all your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>important documents</a> or relevant authorities can upload the documents to your Digi-Locker. To upload the documents n individual needs to scan their <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>important documents</a> in the following formats:</p><p><li>PDF</li><li>JPEG</li><li>PNG</li></p><p>Once the documents are uploaded, they can be accessed anywhere. You will however need to use the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>e-sign</a> facility to sign the documents; this is similar to the process of self-attesting the hard copies of your original documents. Government departments like income tax authorities, CBSE, highway ministry, road transport authorities and organization who get themselves registered with Digi-Locker can push your digital documents to your respective lockers. These documents are accepted by the authorities at various places, like airports where you require identification and other such services.</p><p>There is a mobile application as well as a website available for using Digi-Locker. You can upload your documents through either of the two options available. Once all your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>important documents</a> are uploaded to Digi-Locker you need not carry the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>physical documents</a> with you. </p><p>To open a Digi-Locker account, simply go the website or you can download the Digi-Locker app on your phone through registered mobile number. You can choose your user identification via the OTP. Once you open the account you will be able to upload your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>important documents</a> immediately. You will also see documents that have been pushed by registered organizations in your account if any. You also get an option to create a link for sharing the documents in electronic format with other individuals or organizations.</p><p>Individual use the Digi-Locker for storing of various documents like <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>mark sheets</a>, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>driving licence</a>, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>passport</a>, income tax returns, ration card, birth certificate, school leaving certificate, domicile certificate, caste certificate etc. </p><p>For detailed information one needs to visit the Digi-Locker website at the following link. <a href='https://digilocker.gov.in/'>https://digilocker.gov.in/</a></p><p>Now that you have the option to upload your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>important documents</a> and use them, it is time to go <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>paperless</a> wherever possible, thus eliminating unnecessary administrative work and spending.</p>",
