    //         title: "Lock and unlock online the biometric details of your Aadhar Card",
    //         content: "<div class='blog-content'><p><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a> is now become the single most important document for an individual. This document is used as <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>proof of identity</a> in various applications for the purpose of <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>verification</a>. An individual can use the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a>, for obtaining a SIM card, or for securing admission to a school for one’s children, etc.  The <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a> is a twelve digit number against which your credentials are stored in a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>biometric format</a>. When you apply for a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a>, your fingerprints and your retina scan are stored by the govt. in their secure servers.</p><p>This data can be misused if it falls into the wrong hands. It is imperative that one takes necessary steps to secure this data. The government has now provided the option to lock the biometric details of your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a> using their online website. Once you lock the biometric details online, even the owner of the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a> cannot access the information on the servers. You can however unlock the same temporarily or you can also disable the lock till such time you need to relock it.</p><p>First and foremost you have to ensure that your link your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>registered mobile number</a> with Aadhar. This is important as you will receive your OTP (One Time Password) on this mobile number for the purpose of locking and unlocking your biometric details.</p><p>We will outline the steps on how to lock and unlock your biometric details online.<li>Go to the Aadhar website <a class='link' href='https://uidai.gov.in/' target='_blank'>https://uidai.gov.in/</a></li><li>On the home page of the website you will need to click on <a href='https://resident.uidai.gov.in/biometric-lock' target='_blank' class='link'>Lock/Unlock Biometrics</a></li><li>On clicking the above, you will be redirected to the following page <a href='https://resident.uidai.gov.in/biometric-lock' target='_blank' class='link'>https://resident.uidai.gov.in/biometric-lock</a></li><li>Enter the 12 digit <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Aadhar card</a> number on the page and the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>security code</a> and then click on Send OTP (see image below)<br><div class='image-section'><img src='img/blogs/step1.png' class='img-responsive'></div></li><li>Once you receive the OTP, enter it on the same page and click on Login</li><li>Once you are logged in, you need to enter the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>security code</a> shown on the page and click on “Enable”  (see image below)<br><div class='image-section'><img src='img/blogs/step2.png' class='img-responsive'></div></li><li>You will receive the following message (see image below)<br><div class='image-section'><img src='img/blogs/step3.png' class='img-responsive'></div></li></p><p>You can disable or unlock temporarily when required, by again visiting the link <a href='https://resident.uidai.gov.in/biometric-lock' target='_blank' class='link'>https://resident.uidai.gov.in/biometric-lock</a> and then do the same steps as above, except that you will now click on “Disable” instead of “Enable”</p><p>That’s it, that is all there is to lock and unlock your biometric details online. Now that you know the simple steps to do the same, stay safe by locking your details as soon as possible and unlock the same only when required.</p></div>",
