    //         title: "Know your bank balance using your smart phone without internet",
    //         content: "<div class='blog-content'><p>Most of the people today have a smart phone which is connected to the internet. Internet banking has been around for quite some time now and has been used for various activities, like checking of bank balance, transferring money and a host of other things. Internet banking was used primarily on laptops or desktops or hand held tablets. However with the advent of smart phones, most of the banks have developed mobile apps, which can carry out most of the tasks that internet banking can do. These mobile apps too require internet connectivity.</p><p>There may be times when you may not have internet or have poor internet connectivity, or some of the rural population could not be using a smart phone. In such cases, there are certain basic transactions that can be carried out on the phone even without internet connectivity. There are two methods by which you can access basic banking transactions like checking the balance amount in your account, on your GSM handsets.</p><p><strong>Option 1:</strong> You can give a missed call from your mobile handset to the toll free number of the respective bank. Please note that you will have to get the mobile number registered with the respective banks where you hold you’re banking accounts. This same number also needs to be linked with your Aadhar card as well. If you give a missed call from a non-registered mobile number you will receive a message Once you have registered your mobile number, you need to give a missed call to the respective banks number (you can obtain these numbers from the websites of respective banks).</p><p>After you give a call from your registered cell phone number, you can disconnect the call in two to three rings, alternatively the call will get auto terminated after a couple of rings. After some time you will receive an SMS on your phone with the balance in your account and the details of your last five transactions.</p><p>As a customer of the bank you may have different types of accounts with the bank. In such a scenario the default account will get selected in the following sequence:<li>Savings Account</li><li>Current Account</li><li>Over Draft</li><li>Cash Credit</li><li>Other Accounts</li></p><p>In case you have to similar type accounts with the same bank then the account which you have opened lately will be chosen as the default account.</p><p><strong>Option 2:</strong> For GSM phone users, you can <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>dial *99#</a>. This feature was introduced by <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>NPCI</a> (National Payment Corporation of India). This facility allows bank holders to check their bank balance without any internet connectivity, across India. You can avail the following activities with this feature.</p><p><li>No internet connectivity required</li><li>Service is operational 24/7 and even on holidays</li><li>No need of downloading any software or third party app on your phone</li><li>No roaming charges across India</li><li>All the telecom operators have the common code of *99#</li><li>Twelve languages of India are covered</li></p><p>Steps on how to check bank balance using *99#</p><p><a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>Dial *99#</a> from your mobile handset</p><p>On you handset you will now see a welcome screen</p><p>Enter the first three characters from the bank’s <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IFSC cod</a>e</p><p>On entering the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IFSC code</a> characters, a menu will be displayed containing various options that are enabled by your respective bank. Check the options and accordingly enter the digit against the option. For example Press 1 for obtaining bank balance. Once you press the required digit, the relevant information will be displayed on the screen.</p><p>You can use the *99# option to generate OTP’s for <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>dual factor authentication</a>; it can also be used to generate you MPIN or mobile pin number to verify your financial operations. You can also use it to transfer monies to via the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>IFSC code</a> option or <a href='http://pehlakadam.in/' target='_blank'>MMID</a> or for Aadhar card recipients.</p><p>The above are two ways in which you can obtain bank related data on your mobile handset. While internet connectivity is not required, please note that in order to obtain the data,  you will need to be present in an area where there is mobile network coverage.</p></div>",
