    //         id: "how-to-deal-with-a-job-loss",
    //         title: "How to deal with a job loss",
    //         content: "<p>A <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> is never easy to deal with and the reasons for a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> can be various. You may get the pink slip due to <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>bad performance</a> or due to external factors like the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>economic meltdown</a> of 2008 where lakhs of people were laid of globally. Whatever the reason, one should always be prepared to deal with the same. A <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> impacts your mental, physical and financial health, so it is important to deal with all the three parameters. </p><p>If you every find yourself in a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> situation, do not <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>panic</a>, while it is easier said than done, one needs to assert <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>self-control</a> and view the situation calmly. Do not get paranoid and surround yourself with negativity or negative people. Do not get depressed and resort to alcohol or drugs as this will only further worsen the situation and become a drain on your financial resources. Being calm will help you to assess the situation more rationally.</p><p>Once you have control over your emotions, it is time to start being physically fit. Now that you have time on your hands, exercise on a daily basis. This will help you to keep your mental balance and physical health in check. </p><p>Network with people in your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>existing office</a>, you can also approach your ex-boss for help. It is always advisable to leave any organization on a good note even if you have been asked to leave. Never burn bridges with anyone as you never know when someone may be of assistance. Network with people that you have met over the years, someone somewhere may come up with an opportunity for you.</p><p>Create a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>resume</a> with the latest details and start applying to various companies via job portals or through word of mouth and networking contacts. Do not be hesitant to approach family and friend to check for job opportunities. Upgrade your knowledge and skill set during a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> period, so that you can add value to your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>resume</a>. It also shows that you have not been sitting idle and have the attitude and aptitude for facing tough situations.</p><p>In a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> you can spend time with your family and friends, do not hide the fact that you have lost your job from your near and dear ones, and be candid about the situation. If you feel that you are getting lonely and depressed and are severely stressed, seek advice from a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>counsellor</a>. With the advent of the digital age, counsellors are also available online and you can talk to them in the privacy of your own surroundings.</p><p>Let us also look at some strategies that one can take in case one has to face a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> situation in the future. If you already have a full time job, then start a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>contingency fund</a>. A <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>contingency fund</a> consist of all the spends that you do in a month, which includes your bills for electricity, telephone, internet, grocery, gas etc. It also includes any EMI’s for loans that you may have. Arrive at a monthly figure which you think is absolutely necessary to have. A general rule is to have six times the amount as <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>contingency fund</a>. So keep aside six months of savings, to tide you over in case of a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a>. This will put less drain on your financial resources and also you will not be stressed out so much.</p><p>Try not to exhaust your <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>monthly salary</a>, every month. In case of a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a>, the next job that you apply for may not pay you the same salary and you may have to compromise on the salary. For example if you are currently earning rupees fifty thousand a month and all the money is spent on <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>expenses</a>, then if the next job offered is for rupees forty thousand a month, you will be unable to sustain. Always try to earn a salary that is higher than your expense. While the percentages could be different for different people, it’s a good idea to keep aside between 40 to 50 percent of your salary for savings and the balance for <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>expenses</a>. The way to do this is to start <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>financial planning</a> early and build a good portfolio of investments.</p><p>If you have planned well in advance and are prepared to face any eventualities at times a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>job loss</a> may give you the much needed break to introspect and you may come out stronger with better opportunities. </p>",
