    //         title: "Difference between Rupay, Visa and MasterCard",
    //         content: "<p>The National Payments Corporation of India (<a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>NPCI</a>) launched <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card a few years ago. This is a completely home grown and domestic product. This was launched with an intention to bring the banking facilities to the rural parts of India under the<a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'> Pradhan Mantri Jan Dhan Yojana</a> scheme. Its bigger competitors are VISA, <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a> which have been around for almost four decades and have a huge head start on <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a>. The word <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> is a combination of alphabets from the words Rupee and Payment.</p><p>To obtain a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a>, you have to fill in the application form and request for a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a> when you apply for a bank account. </p><ul><li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> is a certified and approved card <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a> just like VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a>.  However there are difference between <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> and VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a>. While VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Car</a>d have similar features, let us look at the features that are different for the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card.</li><li>The <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card currently is only available in <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a> format whereas VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a> have both debit and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>credit cards</a>. <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> does not have <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>credit cards</a> currently.</li><li>The <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card is a domestic <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a> and cannot be used internationally. So if you are travelling abroad then it is recommended that you have VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master card</a> with you as they can be used internationally as well as in India.</li><li>The <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card does not levy fees for the banks and hence they do not have to pay a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>quarterly charges</a> or joining charges. VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master card</a> levy joining and other charges for banks globally. </li><li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> being a domestic product the end users will be charged less <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>processing fees</a>. VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a> will charge much higher <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>processing fees</a> as the transactions are done internationally.</li><li><a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> has access to a domestic <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a> and hence <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a>s can be used only in the domestic markets. This has certain advantages like, your data will not be sent out of the country and since the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a> is domestic the processing time will be relatively faster. When you use VISA and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Master Card</a> your data is sent out of the country and also the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a> is international the processing times for transactions are longer. Being a domestic <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a> you may be unable to use the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card on online shopping websites, they have an international <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>payment gateway</a>.</li></ul><p>If you are domestic user then you can avail the advantages the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>debit card</a> has to offer. There is a lack of awareness of these advantages for the domestic user. If more and more domestic users start using the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> card this will have an economic advantage for India as the monies and fees will stay within the country. <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>RuPay</a> needs to aggressively market its product to both the rural and urban sector and in time it will evolve to a level where it is at par with its competitors.  The <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>NPCI</a> is working hard to make this happen in the near future</p>",
