    //         title: "Advantages and disadvantages of virtual trading",
    //         content: "<p>Let us understand who the target audience is and what <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> is all about. To answer the first part, the general outlook is that it is intended for beginners or novices in the field of <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a>. While to a large extent that may hold true, but <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> can be used by people who are already <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>traders</a> and are considered to be experts as well. </p><p><a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Virtual tradin</a>g is a platform provided by some <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>brokers</a> or financial institution’s wherein one can simulate the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>real markets </a>in a virtual environment. You can choose the markets that you want to trade in and then look up the prices of the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>stocks</a> and trade in them using <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual cash</a> or currency which is provided by the financial institution. You will be allocated a certain sum of <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual currency</a> which you can use to <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>invest</a> or trade into the virtual markets. You can reset the sum and start all over again if you wish to.</p><p>While most of the financial institution’s charge you a small fee, there are certain institution’s that offer this environment free as well, though the features may be somewhat limited as compared to a paid version. If you are a beginner then the free version should be fine initially, and as you gradually move up the ladder you can opt for the paid version which has more features. Bear in mind while the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> platform or <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> simulator as it is known will be unable to replicate exact and real market conditions. </p><p>Having a fair idea as to what a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a> */ platform is, let us know dive into the aspects of the advantages and the disadvantages that come with using a virtual environment for <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a>.</p><h5>Let us first look at the advantages:</h5><p><strong>No capital risk:</strong>It does not matter if you are a beginner or an expert trader; there is absolutely no risk for capital involved. You can trade any of the markets (provided the institution has the option for the same). You can analyse tons of data related to the market. You get to learn a lot and you can play around with the tools that the virtual platform has to offer. Even if you make</p><p><strong>Testing:</strong> It is a great way to test the ideas that you may have. If you have done a course on <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>technical analysis</a> and are looking at testing what you have learned without carrying the inherent risks that are associated with it, then a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> platform is the right place to do the same. As the virtual platform will provide you with past data of the markets, you can back test them. <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Back testing</a> is a process where you look at the past history of a stock or markets and then apply strategies and test them on the past data and see if the strategies work and the probability of the strategies working in real time when you venture into the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>real markets</a></p><p><strong><a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>Real Time Analysis</a>:</strong> Since the virtual platform is connected to the markets in real time you get a first-hand experience of how the markets function at different stages. And since you are <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a> and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>investing</a> you get to see the complete analysis of your investments and equity portfolio as you would get to see in real time. You can view the actual profit and loss of all your investments, using the built in reports of the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> platform.</p><p><strong>Building confidence:</strong> When you practise regularly on a virtual platform, over a period you can see what worked and what did not. You can then analyse what did not work and take corrective measures for the same. This will give your confidence a boost so that when you step into the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>real markets </a>you will not commit the same mistakes that you did in the virtual environment.</p><h5>Let us know look at some of the disadvantages:</h5><p><strong>Psychological connect:</strong> As there is no risk of losing any money using the virtual platform, you may tend not to take the environment seriously and become complacent. In <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>real markets </a>one should ideally let the profits keep running, while keeping your losses narrow, using tight stop loss techniques. In live markets when you have your own real money invested, the pressures on the mind can be immense depending on one’s temperament. In a virtual environment there is no stress and hence the focus and discipline may be lacking.</p><p><strong>Fees and <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>brokerages</a>:</strong> There are no charges like <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>brokerages</a>, slippages or <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>margin money</a> to be maintained with the broker. While <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a> in a virtual environment you may not account for these fees and thus end up with inflated profits. One needs to check what the various charges are in a real trade and apply them to the virtual environment as well to arrive at a correct profit and loss statement.</p><p><strong>Market conditions:</strong> There are numerous external factors which influence the markets in a real world, which may be difficult to replicate in a virtual environment. The price of the <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>stocks</a> and markets are also governed by <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>stock markets</a> the world over. So if you are <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>trading</a> the markets in India, then even after market hours, there are indices from other countries in different time zones that are working and may affect the price, causing volatility in the Indian markets the next day. These may not reflect in the virtual platform, leading to a false sense of security.</p><p>Beginners should take complete advantage of the virtual platform to hone their skills. The only thing that is required is focus and discipline. The experts too can use this to test complex or new theories and strategies that they may come across. The above are some of the primary advantages and disadvantages of using a <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>virtual trading</a> platform. It is advisable to do you research and find a broker or institution which has low fees and provides real time market data without a time lag so that you can test your theories and strategies in almost real time <a href='http://pehlakadam.in' target='_blank'>market conditions</a>.</p>",
